adUsrAccessEntry.name: adUsrAccessEntry
adUsrAccessEntry.description: Extended table from adminUserTable. The values from adminUserAccess column take higher precedence and this table entry will be considered only when the adminUserAccess column from adminUserTable has a value of 'intermediate'. This table is to configure the various level of administrator privilages. This is mainly for admin who try to manage BSCs using Web interfaces. Every column in this table correspond to a tab name in web interface. So choosing enable/disable will grant/deny access to the administrator user for the corresponding tabs. Note: The administrator with the username as 'admin have all access and considered as the the super user for BSCs
